1. Used bootstrap to center and make the content responsive
2. Used bootstrap buttons instead of basic HTML buttons  
3. Used bootstraps responsive 12-column grid system. An example of this is using 'col-xs-*' where 'xs' means to use a 
small row and '*' is replaced with 4 because this means we want the grid to be 4 wide.

4. Used bootstrap CSS instead of conventional CSS such as 'text-primary' and 'img-responsive' bootstrap classes.
5. Used 'span' to put several elements on the same line. 
6. Used Bootstraps icon and vector library to add custom i tag icons. 
7. ensured all contianers and elements were responsive by utilizing "container-fluid" bootstrap class. 
